Rule: Higher levels of education (Bachelors, Prof-school, Doctorate) are associated with a higher likelihood of earning more than $50k per year.
A shift to a Professional occupation is associated with a higher likelihood of earning more than $50k per year.
Older age does not necessarily preclude earning more than $50k per year.
Hours per week does not show a clear pattern, indicating that other factors might play a more significant role in income prediction.
